A vintage 1960s-era technical illustration depicting a complex mechanical view-master device merged with an early computer terminal, rendered in warm sepia and amber tones with subtle halftone dot patterns. The view-master contains multiple rotating carousel layers showing miniature architectural floor plans and data grids visible through its circular viewing windows. Delicate brass gears and copper wiring connect the device to a series of cascading index card filing systems that transform into flowing digital streams. The composition suggests the metamorphosis of traditional organization systems into something more sophisticated. Aged paper texture throughout, with subtle coffee stains at the edges and the aesthetic of a patent drawing or vintage engineering manual.
